rComments: Very well organized.  Exceptionally clear Great command of   the  subject matter
He is very approachable and has sparked my interest in the subject. We need more professors like him at this school. Very fair grading if you put the effort in.
Excellent in every respect!! He knows his stuff so well and his lectures are a treat. So sweet to listen.

Course coordinator for Tamil Studies... most disorganized course ever. Had no real marking schemes... assignments never given back on time. Had a lot of guest lecturers, which was good but did nothing to pull anything together. Would be incredibly hard for a student with no tamil cultural background. Needs to rework the whole course.

Very interesting course. Professor is very helpful and encourages students who are  keen to learn. He is a superb scholar. I have decided to do all the  courses that he is teaching. If all professors are like him university education will be a great experience.

Excellent Teacher. I followed three of his courses in U of T. Marvellous lectures. Gentle and helpful but gives a real hard intellectual slap right on the face to those students who are habitually deceitful and fradulent. I wish all professors are like him.

This is one of the best courses I ever did. Remarakable Professor, exceptionally knowledgeable and effective communicator. But strict disciplinarian. Majority of students admired him, odd ones resented. If a student wanted to play the truant and have her way,   with this Prof. there is no space for cheating. We need more like him.
This teacher is a complete jerk and he will take your passion for learning, squeeze the dignity out of it and then slap you on the face with it. He's not a hard marker but its not worth it.!!
